From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dynamic Devices <support@dynamicdevices.co.uk>
Date: Sun, 25 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: fsl_sai: mirror Rx frame to Tx on capture-only (DT510)

On DT510 driver mic (TAA5412 on &sai5) LRCLK is muxed to SAI5_TX_SYNC while
only the Rx path carries ADC data. During arecord-only the Tx frame size/word
config must match Rx or LRCLK toggle rate diverges from sample rate (MSO ~72 kHz
vs 48 kHz with correct 3.072 MHz BCLK). Mirror TCR4/TCR5 from capture hw_params
when the active stream is Rx.

Signed-off-by: Dynamic Devices <support@dynamicdevices.co.uk>
---
 sound/soc/fsl/fsl_sai.c | 18 ++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 18 insertions(+)

diff --git a/sound/soc/fsl/fsl_sai.c b/sound/soc/fsl/fsl_sai.c
--- a/sound/soc/fsl/fsl_sai.c
+++ b/sound/soc/fsl/fsl_sai.c
@@ -683,6 +683,24 @@ static int fsl_sai_hw_params(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream,
 	regmap_write(sai->regmap, FSL_SAI_xMR(tx),
 		     ~0UL - ((1 << min(channels, slots)) - 1));
 
+	/*
+	 * Capture-only with FS/LRCK on TX_SYNC (DT510 SAI5 / TAA5412): program
+	 * Tx frame size and word width to match Rx so LRCLK = BCLK / (slots *
+	 * slot_width). The sync helper above does not always run for this wiring.
+	 */
+	if (!sai->is_consumer_mode && !tx) {
+		regmap_update_bits(sai->regmap, FSL_SAI_TCR4(ofs),
+				   FSL_SAI_CR4_SYWD_MASK | FSL_SAI_CR4_FRSZ_MASK |
+				   FSL_SAI_CR4_CHMOD_MASK,
+				   val_cr4 | FSL_SAI_CR4_CHMOD);
+		regmap_update_bits(sai->regmap, FSL_SAI_TCR5(ofs),
+				   FSL_SAI_CR5_WNW_MASK | FSL_SAI_CR5_W0W_MASK |
+				   FSL_SAI_CR5_FBT_MASK, val_cr5);
+		regmap_write(sai->regmap, FSL_SAI_TMR,
+			      ~0UL - ((1 << min(channels, slots)) - 1));
+	}
+
 	return 0;
 }
 
